        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): expose spooled handler timeout config",
        "body": "## Summary\n- expose `channels.telegram.spooledUpdateHandlerTimeoutMs` with top-level and per-account config support\n- pass the configured value into Telegram isolated polling sessions\n- document the timeout and regenerate bundled channel config metadata\n\n## Why\nTelegram isolated ingress already fails stale claimed spool updates after a handler timeout, but operators could not tune that timeout from `channels.telegram`. A wedged `.processing` file can therefore keep a same-chat lane blocked until the default 25 minute timeout.\n\n## Runtime Proof\nI ran a redacted local runtime harness against the PR head using the real `TelegramPollingSession`, real spool files, real reply-fence timeout recovery path, and a fake Telegram Bot runtime to avoid live network calls. The harness configured `isolatedIngress.spooledUpdateHandlerTimeoutMs = 200`, wrote two same-lane spooled updates, wedged update `42`, and verified update `43` drained only after timeout recovery restarted isolated ingress.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"configuredTimeoutMs\": 200,\n  \"configuredAbortGraceMs\": 200,\n  \"elapsedMs\": 475,\n  \"workerCreateCount\": 2,\n  \"botConstructCount\": 2,\n  \"events\": [\n    \"first:42\",\n    \"second:43\"\n  ],\n  \"failedUpdateIds\": [\n    42\n  ],\n  \"pendingUpdateIds\": [],\n  \"timeoutLog\": \"[telegram] Telegram isolated polling spool handler timed out behind update 42 on lane telegram:-100:topic:10 after 205ms; marking the update failed, aborting active reply work, and restarting isolated ingress so later updates can drain.\"\n}\n```\n\nThis shows the configured timeout was honored by the isolated-ingress runtime path: update `42` was failed after the configured timeout budget and the later same-lane update `43` drained after the restart.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm config:channels:check`\n- `pnpm exec vitest run extensions/telegram/src/config-schema.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/polling-session.test.ts` passed locally while preparing the patch. A later rerun in this workspace timed out in Vitest/Rolldown pre-test bundling with repeated plugin timing warnings before any assertion output.",
